<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <style>
        .cta-button {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 12px 24px;
            background-color: #0078d4;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        
        .cta-button:hover {
            background-color: #106ebe;
        }
        
        .hero {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 60px 20px;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        
        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 2.5em;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        
        .hero p {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }
        
        .features {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        
        .feature-card {
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        
        .user-welcome {
            background-color: #e6f7ff;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>My Node.js Web App</h1>
    </header>
    
    <main>
        <% if (isAuthenticated) { %>
        <div class="user-welcome">
            <div>
                <p>Welcome back, <strong><%= user.name %></strong>!</p>
                <p>You're currently signed in.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <a href="/dashboard" class="cta-button">Go to Dashboard</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <% } %>
        
        <section class="hero">
            <h1>Welcome to My Node.js Web App</h1>
            <p>A powerful application with Azure Entra ID authentication and a secure dashboard.</p>
            <% if (!isAuthenticated) { %>
            <a href="/login-page" class="cta-button">Sign In</a>
            <% } %>
        </section>
        
        <div class="features">
            <div class="feature-card">
                <h2>Secure Authentication</h2>
                <p>Powered by Azure Entra ID for enterprise-grade security.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature-card">
                <h2>Interactive Dashboard</h2>
                <p>Access your personalized dashboard after authentication.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="feature-card">
                <h2>Development Mode</h2>
                <p>Built-in mock authentication system for easy local testing.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <section>
            <h2>About This Application</h2>
            <p>This Node.js web application demonstrates Azure Entra ID integration with a clean separation between public and protected content.</p>
            <p>The application features:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Secure authentication flow with Azure Entra ID</li>
                <li>Protected dashboard for authenticated users</li>
                <li>Development mockup for easy local testing</li>
                <li>Session management for persistent login</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
    
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 My Node.js Web App</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>